// Regression floor for the bare-reference-class-field auto-construction bug
// (found + fixed 2026-07-14 while building this corpus). info.md §3 promises
// "every type has a nullary construction path" and a bare field declaration
// auto-constructs — but a bare *reference-class* field with no initializer
// used to keep a void default, so reading through it printed nothing on
// run/ir/llvm (exit 0, no diagnostic) and SEGFAULTED on emit-C++. The fix
// (src/Symbols.hpp bareFieldAutoConstructs + Eval::initFields + Lowerer::
// synthesizeInit) auto-constructs a bare reference-class field exactly as it
// already did value structs, guarded against self-referential types that have
// no finite default (see bare_class_field_selfref_default.lev).
class Inner { int x = 5; }
class Outer { Inner i; }             // bare reference-class field
class Mid { Inner a; }
class Deep { Mid m; }                // acyclic chain, each level auto-constructs
void main() {
    Outer o = Outer();
    console.writeln(o.i.x);          // 5 — i auto-constructed
    Deep d = Deep();
    console.writeln(d.m.a.x);        // 5 — the whole chain auto-constructed
}
main();
